pirical reasonableness, Kleist releases Kant's ethics and doctrine of the sublime from the moderating pull of their examples.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aPhilosophy, Germany19th century. 4aPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Epistemology.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804768269zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804768269423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804768269/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles